Step 3 signature

In[148]:
import numpy as np
from skimage.measure import regionprops
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# 
def get_main_contour(mask):
    from skimage.measure import label
    labeled = label(mask)
    regions = regionprops(labeled)
    max_area = 0
    main_region = None
    for region in regions:
        if region.area > max_area:
            max_area = region.area
            main_region = region
    return main_region

# 
def calculate_signature(edge_mask):
    # 
    main_region = get_main_contour(edge_mask)
    
    # 
    cy, cx = main_region.centroid
    
    # 
    edge_points = np.argwhere(edge_mask)
    
    # 
    angles = []
    radii = []
    for (y, x) in edge_points:
        dx = x - cx
        dy = y - cy
        radius = np.sqrt(dx**2 + dy**2)
        angle = np.arctan2(-dy, dx)  # -
        angles.append(np.degrees(angle))  # 
        radii.append(radius)
    
    # 0-360
    angles = np.array(angles) % 360
    
    # 
    sorted_indices = np.argsort(angles)
    sorted_angles = angles[sorted_indices]
    sorted_radii = np.array(radii)[sorted_indices]
    
    # 
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 4), dpi=300)
    plt.plot(sorted_angles, sorted_radii, linewidth=1)
    plt.title('Edge Signature')
    plt.xlabel('Angle (degrees)')
    plt.ylabel('Distance from Center')
    plt.grid(True)
    plt.show()
    
    return sorted_angles, sorted_radii

# 
signature_angles, signature_radii = calculate_signature(edge_morph)

def plot_coordinate_system(mask):
    # 
    main_region = get_main_contour(mask)
    cy, cx = main_region.centroid
    
    # 
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 8), dpi=300)
    plt.imshow(mask, cmap='gray')
    
    # 
    plt.scatter(cx, cy, c='red', marker='*', s=100, label='Center')
    
    # XY
    axis_length = max(mask.shape)//4
    plt.arrow(cx, cy, axis_length, 0, color='r', width=2, head_width=10)
    plt.arrow(cx, cy, 0, -axis_length, color='b', width=2, head_width=10)  # Y
    
    # 
    plt.text(cx+axis_length+40, cy, 'X (0)', color='red', ha='center', va='center')
    plt.text(cx, cy-axis_length-30, 'Y (90)', color='blue', ha='center', va='center')
    plt.title('Tumor with Coordinate System')
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.legend()
    plt.show()

# 
plot_coordinate_system(tumor_mask_uint8)

Project 2: Texture feature

  • Use the provided data of brain tumor MRI
    • Extract the tumor region with the provided mask
    • For the tumor region, rescale the region to 128 levels, compute and display GLCM with a operator along x axis (1 pixel to the right) and along y axis (1 pixel down) respectively
    • Compute the homogeneity, contrast, uniformity(energy) of GLCM.
  • Conduct analysis above once again for the normal part from other part of the brain
    • Compare your result with functions in MATLAB(graycoprops) /Python and tell the difference.

Step 2 GLCM

In[150]:
import numpy as np
from skimage.feature import graycomatrix, graycoprops
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def calculate_glcm_features(image, mask, distances=[1], angles=[0, np.pi/2]):
    """
    GLCM
    
        image : 0-1272D uint8
        mask : 2D bool
        distances : 1
        angles : 0pi/2
    
        features: 
        glcm: 
    """
    masked_image = np.zeros_like(image)
    masked_image[mask] = image[mask]  # mask
    
    # ROI
    plt.figure(figsize=(12,5),dpi=300)
    

    plt.subplot(121)
    plt.imshow(image, cmap='gray')
    plt.title('Original MRI Image')

    plt.subplot(122)
    plt.imshow(image, cmap='gray')
    plt.contour(mask, colors='yellow', linewidths=1)  # 
    plt.title('Tumor ROI on Original')
    
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

    # GLCM
    glcm = graycomatrix(masked_image, 
                       distances=distances, 
                       angles=angles,
                       levels=128,
                       symmetric=True, 
                       normed=True)
    
    # 
    features = {'horizontal': {}, 'vertical': {}}
    
    # 
    for i, angle in enumerate(angles):
        key = 'horizontal' if angle == 0 else 'vertical'
        glcm_slice = glcm[:, :, 0, i]
        
        # 
        features[key] = {
            'max_probability': np.max(glcm[:, :, 0, i]),
            'correlation': graycoprops(glcm, 'correlation')[0, i],
            'contrast': graycoprops(glcm, 'contrast')[0, i],
            'energy': graycoprops(glcm, 'energy')[0, i],
            'homogeneity': graycoprops(glcm, 'homogeneity')[0, i],
            'entropy': -np.sum(glcm[:, :, 0, i] * np.log2(glcm[:, :, 0, i] + 1e-12))
        }

    return features, glcm

#  -------------------------------------------------
# GLCM
features, glcm = calculate_glcm_features(tumor_img, mask)
